---
title: Szechuan Turkey & Green Bean Stir-Fry with Toasted Cashews & Quinoa
description: Forget takeout: The path to sweet-spicy-savory dinner bliss is as simple as breaking out a frying pan! In this recipe, ground turkey and green beans are coated in tantalizing Szechuan sauce and cashews are toasted to create the perfect crunchy topping. Everything comes together over a bed of steamy white quinoa mixed with warm, sizzly ginger—in only 30 minutes! The results? A symphony of flavors and textures that are so delicious, you might just lick the plate.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/szechuan-turkey-green-bean-stir-fry-9f93ee23.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/szechuan-turkey-green-bean-stir-fry-60ca09357f6a054e404ac8f9-681545f9.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/szechuan-turkey-green-bean-stir-fry-60ca09357f6a054e404ac8f9
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Asian
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 64 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 2140 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary;
cut crosswise into 2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half
the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @water{1%cup} and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then add
@white quinoa{1/2%cup}, cover, and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until quinoa is
tender and water has evaporated, ~{15-20%minutes}. Drain any excess water if
necessary.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While quinoa cooks, add green beans and a splash of water to a #medium
microwave-safe bowl{}; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender,
~{1-2%minutes}. Drain.

Heat a #large pan{} (preferably nonstick) over medium-high heat. Add
@cashews{1/2%ounce}; cook, stirring, until browned and lightly toasted,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for cashews over medium-high heat. Add
@ground turkey{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned,
~{4-6%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Stir green beans, scallion whites, remaining ginger, and @sugar{1%tsp} into pan
with turkey. Cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until ginger
is fragrant and turkey is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, half the @Szechuan paste{2%tablespoon},
and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until everything is thoroughly coated,
~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

Fluff quinoa with a #fork{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide
between #bowls{}.

Taste and season turkey stir-fry with salt and pepper; spoon over rice. Sprinkle
with scallion greens and cashews. Serve.

> For 4 servings, use 2 cups water and 1 tsp salt for cooking quinoa, and 2 tsp
> sugar in the stir-fry. Use all the Szechuan paste and 1/3 cup water in the sauce.